### ===========================================
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS - COMPREHENSIVE TESTS
### ===========================================
###
### This file tests Laravel Fortify authentication endpoints
### Test both success and failure cases for each endpoint
###
### SETUP:
### 1. Make sure your Laravel app is running (php artisan serve)
### 2. Update @baseUrl below to match your server
### 3. Database should be migrated and seeded
###
### ===========================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiPrefix = 
@testEmail = testuser@example.com
@testPassword = Password123!
@testName = Test User


### ===========================================
### 1. REGISTRATION TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 1.1: Successful Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "{{testName}}",
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "password_confirmation": "{{testPassword}}",
  "terms": true
}

###

### Test 1.2: Registration - Missing Required Fields
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "",
  "password": ""
}

###

### Test 1.3: Registration - Invalid Email Format
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "password_confirmation": "{{testPassword}}"
}

###

### Test 1.4: Registration - Password Mismatch
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "password_confirmation": "DifferentPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 1.5: Registration - Duplicate Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "password_confirmation": "{{testPassword}}"
}

###

### Test 1.6: Registration - Weak Password (if validation exists)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "weakpass@example.com",
  "password": "123",
  "password_confirmation": "123"
}

###


### ===========================================
### 2. LOGIN TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 2.1: Successful Login
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "remember": false
}

###

### Test 2.2: Login - Invalid Credentials (Wrong Password)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 2.3: Login - Non-existent Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}"
}

###

### Test 2.4: Login - Missing Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}"
}

###

### Test 2.5: Login - Missing Password
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": ""
}

###

### Test 2.6: Login with Remember Me
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}",
  "remember": true
}

###


### ===========================================
### 3. LOGOUT TEST
### ===========================================
### Note: You'll need to be authenticated first (run successful login)

### Test 3.1: Successful Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 3.2: Logout - Unauthenticated User
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

###


### ===========================================
### 4. FORGOT PASSWORD TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 4.1: Successful Forgot Password Request
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/forgot-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}"
}

###

### Test 4.2: Forgot Password - Non-existent Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/forgot-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com"
}

###

### Test 4.3: Forgot Password - Invalid Email Format
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/forgot-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "invalid-email-format"
}

###

### Test 4.4: Forgot Password - Missing Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/forgot-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": ""
}

###


### ===========================================
### 5. RESET PASSWORD TESTS
### ===========================================
### Note: You'll need a valid reset token from the forgot password email

@resetToken = PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL_HERE

### Test 5.1: Successful Password Reset
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/reset-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "token": "{{resetToken}}",
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "NewPassword123!",
  "password_confirmation": "NewPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 5.2: Reset Password - Invalid Token
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/reset-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "token": "invalid-token-12345",
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "NewPassword123!",
  "password_confirmation": "NewPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 5.3: Reset Password - Password Mismatch
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/reset-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "token": "{{resetToken}}",
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "NewPassword123!",
  "password_confirmation": "DifferentPassword123!"
}

###

### Test 5.4: Reset Password - Missing Token
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/reset-password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "NewPassword123!",
  "password_confirmation": "NewPassword123!"
}

###


### ===========================================
### 6. EMAIL VERIFICATION TESTS
### ===========================================
### Note: Requires authenticated user with unverified email

### Test 6.1: Get Email Verification Notice (Unauthenticated)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/email/verify HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

###

### Test 6.2: Resend Verification Email
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/email/verification-notification HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 6.3: Resend Verification Email - Unauthenticated
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/email/verification-notification HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

###

### Test 6.4: Verify Email with Link (GET)
### Note: Replace {id} and {hash} with actual values from verification email
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/email/verify/1/HASH_FROM_EMAIL?expires=TIMESTAMP&signature=SIGNATURE HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###


### ===========================================
### 7. USER PROFILE / CURRENT USER TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 7.1: Get Current Authenticated User (Sanctum API)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Test 7.2: Get Current User - Unauthenticated
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json

###


### ===========================================
### 8. TWO-FACTOR AUTHENTICATION TESTS
### ===========================================
### Note: Requires 2FA to be enabled for the user

### Test 8.1: Enable Two-Factor Authentication
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/two-factor-authentication HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 8.2: Get Two-Factor QR Code
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/two-factor-qr-code HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 8.3: Get Two-Factor Secret Key
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/two-factor-secret-key HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 8.4: Get Two-Factor Recovery Codes
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/two-factor-recovery-codes HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###

### Test 8.5: Confirm Two-Factor Authentication
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/confirmed-two-factor-authentication HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

{
  "code": "123456"
}

###

### Test 8.6: Confirm 2FA - Invalid Code
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/confirmed-two-factor-authentication HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

{
  "code": "000000"
}

###

### Test 8.7: Two-Factor Challenge - Valid Code
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/two-factor-challenge HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "code": "123456"
}

###

### Test 8.8: Two-Factor Challenge - Recovery Code
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/two-factor-challenge HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "recovery_code": "recovery-code-here"
}

###

### Test 8.9: Disable Two-Factor Authentication
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user/two-factor-authentication HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest
Cookie: XSRF-TOKEN=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE; laravel_session=YOUR_SESSION_HERE

###


### ===========================================
### 9. GOOGLE OAUTH TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 9.1: Redirect to Google OAuth
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google HTTP/1.1
Accept: text/html

###

### Test 9.2: Google OAuth Callback (manual test required)
### Note: This should be tested in a browser
### URL: {{baseUrl}}/auth/google/callback
###


### ===========================================
### 10. RATE LIMITING TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 10.1: Rate Limit - Multiple Login Attempts
### Run this multiple times quickly (>5 times in a minute)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Requested-With: XMLHttpRequest

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

###


### ===========================================
### 11. CSRF PROTECTION TESTS
### ===========================================

### Test 11.1: Get CSRF Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/sanctum/csrf-cookie HTTP/1.1

###

### Test 11.2: Login without CSRF Token (should fail for web routes)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "{{testEmail}}",
  "password": "{{testPassword}}"
}

###


### ===========================================
### NOTES FOR TESTING
### ===========================================
###
### 1. For authenticated requests, you need to:
###    - First run successful login test
###    - Copy cookies from response (XSRF-TOKEN and laravel_session)
###    - Paste them in the Cookie header
###
### 2. For API token requests (Sanctum):
###    - Create a token via Laravel Tinker: User::find(1)->createToken('test')->plainTextToken
###    - Use it in Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN header
###
### 3. Expected Response Codes:
###    - 200/201: Success
###    - 302/303: Redirect (for web routes)
###    - 401: Unauthenticated
###    - 403: Forbidden
###    - 419: CSRF token mismatch
###    - 422: Validation error
###    - 429: Too many requests (rate limit)
###
### 4. Email Verification:
###    - Check your email or use a tool like Mailtrap
###    - Or check database: password_reset_tokens table
###
### 5. For Google OAuth:
###    - Must be tested in a browser due to redirect flow
###    - Ensure GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID and GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET are set in .env
###
### ===========================================
